<h1>@HI{{kadouka}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>


<p>
<dl>
<dt>(A)
<ol>
<li><em>interrogative</em> @Vplain{{}}<strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong>, ... 
<li><em>interrogative</em> @Ai{{}}<strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong>, ...
<li><em>interrogative</em> @Anastem{{}}<strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong>, ...
<li><em>interrogative</em> @N{{}}<strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong>, ...
</ol>
<dt>(B)
<ol>
<li><em>yes-no</em> @Vplain{{}}<strong>@HI{{kadouka}}</strong>, ...
<li><em>yes-no</em> @Ai{{}}<strong>@HI{{kadouka}}</strong>, ...
<li><em>yes-no</em> @Anastem{{}}<strong>@HI{{kadouka}}</strong>, ...
<li><em>yes-no</em> @N{{}}<strong>@HI{{kadouka}}</strong>, ...
</ol>
</dl>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
In sentence pattern (A) a question with an interrogative is embedded in another sentence. Note that, optionally, 
<strong>@HI{{kadouka}}</strong> can be used in this sentence pattern.
</p>

<p>
In sentence pattern (B) a question <em>without</em> an interrogative is embedded in another sentence. Note that 
<strong>@HI{{kadouka}}</strong> <em>must</em> be used in this sentence pattern.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      JL107@HI{{@KJ{{convenience}}ha @KJ{{what^time}}ni @KJ{{arrival^don}}suru<strong>ka</strong>,
      @KJ{{tune}}bete kudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please check what time JL107 will arrive.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{sono@KJ{{tale}}ha hountou <strong>ka douka</strong>, wakarimasenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I don't know whether the story is true or not.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

